						<summary>

						<p>This is not dated. It records that king <hi rend="bold">Achyutarāya-Mahārāya</hi> made a gift of the village, <hi rend="bold">Chiṭikanahāḷu,</hi> for offerings to the god Prasanna-Virūpāksha at <hi rend="bold">Jentegal.</hi> The gift was made for the merit of his father <hi rend="bold">Narasṇṇa-Nāyaka</hi> and was recorded on a copper-plate. <hi rend="italic">Liṅgamudre</hi> stones were set up on the boundaries of the village.</p>						

						</summary>
